@startuml Component Diagram - Cross-Cutting: Error Handling & Audit Logging (Simplified)
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml
title Cross-Cutting Concerns: Error Handling & AGID Audit Compliance

Container_Boundary(renderer, "Renderer Process (Angular)") {

    ' Domain services
    Component(import_svc, "Import Service", "Service", "Load operations")
    Component(search_svc, "Search Service", "Service", "Search operations")
    Component(export_svc, "Export Service", "Service", "Export operations")
    Component(verify_svc, "Verification Service", "Service", "Verify operations")

    ' Infrastructure services
    Component(error_handler, "Error Handler", "Service", "Error classification\n• Validation\n• Network\n• User\n• Recovery")
    
    Component(perf_monitor, "Performance Monitor", "Service", "Latency tracking\n• Response time\n• Duration\n• SLA check")
    
    Component(audit_logger, "Audit & Logging", "Service", "AGID compliance\n• User operations\n• Timestamps\n• Event context")
    
    Component(notification_svc, "Notification Service", "Service", "User feedback\n• Error alerts\n• Status messages")
}

Container_Boundary(main, "Main Process (Node.js)") {
    Component(audit_storage, "Audit Log Storage", "Persistent", "Non-repudiation\nCompliance record")
}

' Error flow
Rel(import_svc, error_handler, "report errors")
Rel(search_svc, error_handler, "report errors")
Rel(export_svc, error_handler, "report errors")
Rel(verify_svc, error_handler, "report errors")

Rel(error_handler, notification_svc, "notify user")
Rel(error_handler, audit_logger, "log: error")

' Performance flow
Rel(import_svc, perf_monitor, "measure")
Rel(search_svc, perf_monitor, "measure")
Rel(export_svc, perf_monitor, "measure")
Rel(verify_svc, perf_monitor, "measure")

Rel(perf_monitor, audit_logger, "enrich with metrics")

' Audit flow  
Rel(import_svc, audit_logger, "log: load/select")
Rel(search_svc, audit_logger, "log: search")
Rel(export_svc, audit_logger, "log: export")
Rel(verify_svc, audit_logger, "log: verify")

Rel(audit_logger, audit_storage, "persist logs")

note as cross_cutting
  **Cross-Cutting Concerns: Errors & Audit**
  
  Error Handling Flow:
  1. Service encounters error
  2. Reports to ErrorHandler
  3. ErrorHandler classifies error type
  4. Notifies user via NotificationService
  5. Logs error via AuditLogger
  
  Audit Logging Flow:
  1. Service performs operation
  2. Reports metrics to PerformanceMonitor
  3. Reports operation to AuditLogger
  4. AuditLogger enriches with:
     - Operation type
     - Timestamp
     - Duration (from PerformanceMonitor)
     - Error status (from ErrorHandler)
  5. Sends log to Main Process
  6. Main Process persists to storage
  
  AGID Compliance:
  ✓ Non-repudiation: All actions logged with timestamps
  ✓ Audit trail: Complete operation history
  ✓ SLA tracking: Performance metrics captured
  ✓ Error tracking: All failures recorded
  ✓ Persistence: Logs stored in Main Process
  
  Services NOT directly coupled:
  • Domain services don't know about logging
  • Error handler doesn't know about audit
  • Performance monitor is independent
  • Clean separation of concerns
  
  Coordination via dependency injection:
  constructor(
    private errorHandler: IErrorHandler,
    private auditLogger: IAuditLogger,
    private performanceMonitor: IPerformanceMonitor
  ) { }
end note

@enduml
